### Configure Basic CodeBlock in Payload Lexical Rich Text Editor

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/official-features.mdx

Demonstrates how to import and configure the `CodeBlock` feature for Payload CMS Lexical rich text editor. This setup enables syntax highlighting, sets a default language (TypeScript), and provides a list of supported languages like JavaScript and Plain Text for users to select.

```ts
import { BlocksFeature, CodeBlock } from '@payloadcms/richtext-lexical'

// ...
BlocksFeature({
  blocks: [
    CodeBlock({
      defaultLanguage: 'ts',
      languages: {
        js: 'JavaScript',
        plaintext: 'Plain Text',
        ts: 'TypeScript',
      },
    }),
  ],
}),
// ...
```

